1 Section 2. Section 61-8-327, MCA, is amended to read:
2 "61-8-327. One-way roadways, rotary traffic islands, and roundabouts. (1) The department of
3 transportation or a local authority may designate a highway, roadway, part of a roadway, or specific lanes under
4 its respective jurisdiction for one-way traffic and shall erect official traffic control devices giving notice of that
5 designation.
6 (2) Upon On a roadway designated by official traffic control devices for one-way traffic, a vehicle
7 may be driven only in the direction designated.
8 (3) A vehicle passing around a rotary traffic island or a roundabout may be driven only to the right
9 of the island or the center of the roundabout.
10 (4) For the purposes of this section, a "roundabout" is a circular intersection where all entering
11 traffic must yield to the vehicles within the intersection."
12
13 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Codification instruction. [Section 1] is intended to be codified as an
14 integral part of Title 61, chapter 8, part 3, and the provisions of Title 61, chapter 8, part 3, apply to [section 1].
